
We use the Prefix Sum + HashMap technique.

Time Complexity

O(n) — We traverse the array once and perform constant-time hashmap operations.

Space Complexity

O(n) — The hashmap may store up to n prefix sums in the worst case.

class Solution:
    def findMaxLength(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:
        mp = {0: -1}
        rsum = 0
        max_len = 0

        for i in range(len(nums)):
            num = nums[i]

            if num == 0:
                rsum -= 1
            else:
                rsum += 1

            if rsum in mp:
                max_len = max(max_len, i - mp[rsum])
            else:
                mp[rsum] = i

        return max_len
